  "important_notes": [
    "NetServer and NetClient are both ApplicationListener singletons accessed via global Vars (netServer/netClient)",
    "NetConnection is abstract — concrete impls provided by platform (e.g., SNet for Steam, standard TCP/UDP)",
    "NetConnection.kick() routes through Administration.handleKicked() to record kick duration per UUID+IP",
    "Administration persists player data, bans, kicks, whitelist to Core.settings as JSON (forceSave)",
    "Administration constructor registers built-in chat anti-spam filter and block interaction rate-limit filter",
    "sendChatMessage in NetClient handles both command dispatch (clientCommands) and chat filtering (admins.filterMessage)",
    "Config is a static inner class with a global registry (Config.all) — used for server configuration at runtime",
    "NetClient.sync() sends clientSnapshot (UDP unreliable), ping, and plan snapshots on timers",
    "NetServer.writeEntitySnapshot(Player) sends all entity states via UDP to a player connection",
    "@Remote annotation drives code generation for RPC — targets/variants/unreliable flags vary per method"
  ],

